3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. KRS 150.022 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) The Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources Commission shall consist of nine
6 (9) members, one (1) from each commission district, as set out by the commissioner
7 with the approval of the commission, and not more than five (5) of the same
8 political party.
9 (2) The Governor shall appoint the members of the commission subject to confirmation
10 by the Senate as described in subsection (3) of this section. Each of the members
11 shall be appointed for a term ending on December 31 of the fourth calendar year
12 following his or her appointment. A member whose reappointment is not
13 confirmed by the Senate while it is in session shall vacate his or her seat upon the
14 date of sine die adjournment of the session in which the confirmation was
15 declined. Otherwise,[ except that] a member's term shall continue until his or her
16 successor is duly appointed and confirmed by the Senate, but no later than one (1)
17 year following the expiration of the member's term. If after one (1) year a successor
18 has not been duly appointed and confirmed by the Senate, the commissioner's seat
19 for that district shall be vacant until a successor is duly appointed and confirmed by
20 the Senate. A member shall serve no more than two (2) full terms, not including any
21 partial term that a member may additionally serve. A person who has been
22 convicted of a felony offense, in Kentucky or under the law of any other state, or
23 any other law of the United States shall not be eligible to serve on the commission.
24 (3) (a) Vacancies through the expiration of terms of the members of the commission
25 shall be filled by appointment by the Governor from a list of five (5) names
26 from each commission district, recommended and submitted by the sportsmen
27 of each respective district.
