1 (b) When the term of a member expires, the commissioner shall call a meeting of
2 the sportsmen in that district not later than thirty (30) days prior to the
3 expiration of the member's term. Notice of the meeting shall be given by
4 publication pursuant to KRS Chapter 424.
5 (c) At the meeting, the sportsmen in attendance shall select and submit to the
6 Governor a list of five (5) residents and citizens of the district who have held
7 hunting and fishing licenses in Kentucky or another state for at least the
8 previous five (5) consecutive years, or who have been hunting and fishing in
9 the Commonwealth for the previous five (5) consecutive years while license-
10 exempt under KRS 150.170, and who are well informed on the subject of
11 wildlife conservation and restoration. Each sportsman may vote for one (1)
12 candidate only, and the list submitted to the Governor shall be made up of the
13 names of the five (5) candidates receiving the five (5) highest vote totals.
14 (d) The Governor shall appoint a successor to the member whose term has
15 expired no later than January 20 of the year following the year in which the
16 member's term expired.
17 (4) Upon appointment to the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources Commission,
18 each commissioner shall execute a bond of one thousand dollars ($1,000) in favor
19 of the Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources, the premium on this bond to be
20 paid out of department funds.
21 (5) In the event of vacancies other than by expiration, the Governor shall fill the
22 vacancy for the unexpired part of the term from the names remaining on the list
23 previously submitted for the district from which the vacancy arose. An appointee
24 chosen under this subsection shall not serve on the commission until duly
25 confirmed by the Senate.
26 (6) Each member of the commission shall take the constitutional oath of office.
27 (7) The Governor shall remove any member of the commission for cause under
